└── 


  
To run Taylor-Green test use the following scripts (each one create a different directory)

run.single.multicore.gnu.x	---> single precision, multicore, fused, using GNU compiler
run.single.multicore.intel.x	---> single precision, multicore, fused, using intel compiler
run.single.multicore.nv.x	---> single precision, multicore, fused, using nvidia compiler

run.double.serial.fused.gnu.x	---> double precision, serial, fused, using GNU compiler
run.mixed2.serial.fused.gnu.x	---> mixed precision, serial, fused, using GNU compiler
run.single.serial.fused.gnu.x	---> single precision, serial, fused, using GNU compiler


bgk.input        --> input file used for the simulation
bgk.input.small  --> input file used for the simulation (small one)
plot.gnu         --> gnuplot file to check the results (to modify accordingly)
plot.gnu.small   --> gnuplot file to check the results between original and fused version (GNU)
